{
  "texts": [
    "The task of salient entity extraction (SEE) is to identify entities that are central to a document's overall meaning.",
    "Previous work on SEE has relied on crowdsourcing (Dojchinovski et al., 2016) or user statistics on the web (e.g.",
    "clickstream data, Gamon et al. 2013) to derive salience labels for entities.",
    "In this study, we extend an approach from Dunietz and Gillick (2014), who considered an entity salient if it also appears in a human-written summary or abstract of a news article, and we cover many further genres rather than just news.",
    "Figure 1 shows an example of salient entities in a conversation annotated according to our definition of salience."
  ]
}